 Here we have three lines: one positive slope, one negative slope, and one vertical line. To find the area of the triangle, we need to determine the vertices of the triangle i.e. solve the equations in pairs and pick the solution with positive values of $x$ and $y$. Using this method, we can find the vertices of the triangle. 
